[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rhys Hobbs in court after death of Andrea Lewis in Tonna

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man accused of killing a woman whose body was found at a house in Neath Port Talbot has appeared in court.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Andrea Lewis, 51, was found at the home in Fairyland Road, Tonna, Neath, at about 08:00 GMT on Saturday.
Rhys Trevor Anthony Hobbs, 43, of Tonna, appeared at Swansea Magistrates' Court on Wednesday charged with her murder.
He was remanded in custody and is set to appear at Swansea Crown Court on Friday.
A second man, 46, also arrested in connection with her death, has been released on police bail.
